# Documentation rules

Full protocol is in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) §4–6. Quick reference:

## Where things live

- [`docs/INDEX.md`](../../docs/INDEX.md) — hand-curated map of every doc. Update when adding, renaming, or deprecating a doc.
- [`docs/spec.md`](../../docs/spec.md) — the unified design spec, **single source of truth**.
- [`docs/decisions/`](../../docs/decisions/) — ADRs. Numbered, immutable once accepted. Add only; never edit `Accepted` ADRs — supersede with a new one instead.
- [`docs/architecture/`](../../docs/architecture/) — living technical docs. Rewrite freely.
- [`docs/guides/`](../../docs/guides/) — task-oriented how-tos.
- [`docs/notes/`](../../docs/notes/) — agent-writable memory: open questions, exploration logs, session summaries. Explicitly **not load-bearing**. See `docs/notes/README.md` for the policy.

## Editing `docs/spec.md`

1. Read the relevant sections fully before changing them.
2. Prefer targeted edits. Don't delete numbered headings without updating cross-references.
3. For meaningful changes (architecture, scope, monetization, licensing, user-visible behaviour), also add an ADR in `docs/decisions/`.
4. Update §13 *"What changed vs. the source documents"* so the change log remains accurate.

## Writing new docs

- Don't duplicate content from the spec. Link to the section.
- One topic per file.
- Prefer short, task-framed titles (`pack-authoring.md`, not `how-to-author-packs-a-complete-guide.md`).
- Don't create new top-level folders under `docs/` without prior discussion.
- Add an entry to [`docs/INDEX.md`](../../docs/INDEX.md) in the matching section. The one-liner there should match the doc's frontmatter `summary:`.

## Frontmatter convention

Every markdown file under `docs/` starts with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: <human-readable title>
summary: <one sentence, ~140 chars>
tags: [design, packs, sync, ...]
related:
  - docs/spec.md
  - docs/decisions/0001-....md
status: stable | living | open | accepted | superseded   # context-dependent
---
```

Notes (`docs/notes/`) additionally use `created:` and optionally `updated:` dates, and the status enum `open | resolved | archived`. See [`docs/notes/README.md`](../../docs/notes/README.md).

`AGENTS.md`, the root `README.md`, and `LICENSE` deliberately do **not** have frontmatter — they are entry-point files.

## Promotion paths

Content matures across layers. Promote rather than expand:

- `notes/` → `decisions/` when an open question becomes a decision.
- `notes/` → `architecture/` when exploration becomes a subsystem design.
- `architecture/` or `notes/` → `spec.md` only via an ADR.

`spec.md` and `decisions/` are never demoted. Stale notes are marked `archived`, not deleted.

## Markdown conventions

- ATX headings (`##`), one H1 per file (after the frontmatter).
- Fenced code blocks with language tags.
- Line length: soft-wrap; no hard wrap at 80 columns.
- Relative links between docs; never absolute URLs to this repo.
